  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\nAs noted here: https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/11862#issuecomment-1677585550 in some cases amount is considered invalid bc of strict limit even thought it's correct amount when taking into consideration defined supply and decimal places.\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Mint token with high supply and many decimal places, e.g.:\r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/20650004/300049b4-0a65-4816-9cc0-3b4089c13255)\r\n2. Try to define airdrop of high amount, using also decimal places:\r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/20650004/09426339-8c4f-4e0a-85b3-e6b2419130b9)\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- example: step 1. do X step 2. do Y etc.. -->\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nTotal supply and also decimal places should be taken into account when validating amount.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nStrict limit of 10 characters is used.\r\n\r\n",
